Spoilers ahead!

00:00:11.469 --> 00:00:13.330
Watch out and take care.

00:00:13.330 --> 00:00:17.210
21-year-old Anastasia "Ana" Steele is an English
literature major at Washington State University's

00:00:17.210 --> 00:00:18.690
satellite campus.

00:00:18.690 --> 00:00:22.560
Meek and mild-mannered, she contrasts the
direct and driven Christian Grey, who is the

00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:25.400
27-year old billionaire entrepreneur she's
set to interview.

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:28.860
The man sits atop his towering skyscraper,
ready for his ten-minute interview with Miss

00:00:28.860 --> 00:00:29.860
Kavanaugh.

00:00:29.860 --> 00:00:33.590
But Kate Kavanaugh, Ana's roommate, has fallen
sick, leaving Ana to interview him in her

00:00:33.590 --> 00:00:34.590
stead.

00:00:34.590 --> 00:00:38.080
Kate teases Ana about her wholesome outfit,
and in turn, she kisses Kate's forehead before

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.280
taking her leave.

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:42.850
At the lobby of Mr. Grey's office, Ana is
greeted by a plethora of beautiful blonde

00:00:42.850 --> 00:00:44.780
women wearing sleek and fitted attires.

00:00:44.780 --> 00:00:47.610
Already, she's feeling out of place with her
more homely-looking ensemble.

00:00:47.610 --> 00:00:51.290
It’s quickly made clear that Ana’s not
like other girls, she’s badly dressed.

00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:54.620
But on a more serious note, Ana sticks out
like a sore thumb because she contrasts the

00:00:54.620 --> 00:00:58.330
professional and self-assured women there
with her more fidgety and awkward demeanor.

00:00:58.330 --> 00:01:00.270
One of the women directs Ana to Christian's
room.

00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:04.400
As the door opens, Ana abruptly trips, interrupting
Christian's contemplation by the window.

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:08.880
When Christian approaches her, Ana is immediately
dazed by his overwhelming yet eloquent aura.

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:12.740
Throughout the interview, Christian intently
stares at Ana, making her feel uncomfortable.

00:01:12.740 --> 00:01:16.119
She monotonously reads out the questions that
Kate had prepared, which are unoriginal, to

00:01:16.119 --> 00:01:17.119
say the least.

00:01:17.119 --> 00:01:20.380
But after Christian’s answers, Ana always
has her own little quip for them, showing

00:01:20.380 --> 00:01:23.240
that she has a heaping spoonful of bluntness
to go with her awkwardness.

00:01:23.240 --> 00:01:26.820
For instance, she asks Christian to what he
owes his success, and when Christian answers

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:29.729
that he's good at people, Ana retorts that
maybe he's just lucky.

00:01:29.729 --> 00:01:32.600
And when Christian emphasizes that he has
a way with knowing what makes people tick

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:36.060
and harnessing talented people's efforts,
Ana correctly and openly surmises that he's

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:37.310
a control freak.

00:01:37.310 --> 00:01:39.960
Instead of being offended, Christian seems
amused by Ana.

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:43.040
Given his status, it’s likely that there’s
not much people who have the candor to speak

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:44.040
against him.

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:47.719
Besides, Christian seems to wear his control
freak title with a badge of pride.

00:01:47.719 --> 00:01:51.060
Almost forebodingly, he tells her that he
exercises control in all things.

00:01:51.060 --> 00:01:54.859
After Ana asks if he feels passionate about
the charity projects he does, Christian dismisses

00:01:54.859 --> 00:01:57.009
the projects as a smart business move.

00:01:57.009 --> 00:02:00.469
Unable to hide her disapproval, Ana doubles
down on her question and proposes that Christian

00:02:00.469 --> 00:02:01.779
